snippet: After freeing a Greenpeace crew, Russia finds one of its ships captured by Senegal in a poaching dispute, but Moscow blames Greenpeace.
abstract: Russia is embroiled in a new dispute with Greenpeace International, having just quieted the furor over its seizure of organization ship in the Arctic; feud is over a Russian fishing trawler accused of poaching in coastal waters off Senegal; Senegal has demanded more than $800,000 in fines, while the Russian government has called for a diplomatic resolution; Russia is blaming Greenpeace for the troubles.
lead_paragraph: After freeing a Greenpeace crew, Russia finds one of its ships captured by Senegal in a poaching dispute, but Moscow blames Greenpeace.

headline.main: Greenpeace in New Feud With Russia Over a Ship Seized by Senegal
headline.print_headline: Greenpeace in New Feud With Moscow Over a Ship
